# Git commits and GitHub CLI

## GitHub CLI (`gh`)

Install and authenticate once per machine:

```bash
brew install gh
gh auth login
```

Use `gh` for GitHub tasks (PRs, issues, checks) instead of manual web flows when possible.

Resolve your noreply email after login:

```bash
gh api user --jq '"\(.id)+\(.login)@users.noreply.github.com"'
```

## Git identity — noreply email

Use the GitHub **noreply** address so pushes are not rejected by GH007 (private email protection).

Set **local** repo config (do not use a personal Gmail):

```bash
git config user.name "$(gh api user --jq .login)"
git config user.email "$(gh api user --jq '"\(.id)+\(.login)@users.noreply.github.com"')"
```

Fallback if `gh` is not logged in: `pvjthomas@users.noreply.github.com`

## When committing

1. Verify: `git config user.email` ends with `@users.noreply.github.com`
2. If push fails with GH007 on an unpushed commit:

```bash
git commit --amend --reset-author --no-edit
git push origin HEAD
```

3. Only amend commits that have **not** been pushed yet (unless explicitly requested).

## Do not commit

- Secrets (`.env`, credentials)
- **`.npy` volume arrays** under `breast-cancer-sim/data/` or `brain-cancer-sim/data/` — see below

## Do not upload `.npy` files (agent rule)

**Never `git add` NumPy volume arrays** unless the user explicitly names a specific file and confirms they want it in git.

| Why | Detail |
|-----|--------|
| GitHub limit | Files over **100 MB** are rejected; full MR volumes are often 88–550 MB |
| Handoff pattern | Share binary volumes via **Drive / Slack / `pde-handoff*.zip`**, not git |
| What to commit instead | JSON sidecars (`.json`), `manifest.json`, QC PNGs, CSV metrics, small code |

**Applies to all pipeline outputs**, including:

- `data/processed/raw-extract-philip-chandan/*.npy`
- `data/processed/pde-input-vinesh/*.npy`
- `data/processed/segmentations/*.npy`, `*_mask.npy`, `radiomics-philip-chandan/*.npy`
- Any other `**/data/**/*.npy`

When committing imaging work, stage **code + docs + JSON/PNG/CSV only**. If `git status` shows untracked `.npy` files, leave them unstaged and mention that volumes stay local.

`data/raw/` (DICOM, NIfTI downloads) is also gitignored — never commit raw downloads.
